records.addlTxt:
State files an Amended Information charging the following crimes:   
Count 1 - Possess illegally obtained prescription, contrary to Section 450.11(7)(h) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
Count 2 - Theft, contrary to Section 943.20(1)(a) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
Count 3 - Obstruct officer, contrary to Section 946.41(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes.   
Count 1 and Count 2 - No contest pleas.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 3.  Motion granted.   
Sentences are withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for fifteen (15) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through counseling; 
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
3) Pay costs of action; 
4) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
5) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
6) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
7) Submit DNA sample.  
Minutes.
